Fine COGNACS

COL COURBE V.S.E.P. (Crooked Neck Bottle) 5.49 64.87

Col Courbe, in its interesting crooked neck bottle, is a fine example of the delicacy and aromatic bouquet that can be achieved by a well made Cognac.

ADET IMPERIALE COGNAC . 5.99 68.50

We must start off by saying that the quality is superb and well above the Three Star level. This brandy was originally imported to sell at $8.00 the bottle. The Cognac firm of Adet is a very old house and has long enjoyed a reputation for excellence, particularly in England where their brandies are in great demand. Exceptional delicacy and distinction.

SINGLE CASK UNBLENDED COGNAC 9.98 114.00

Here is an Estate bottled Cognac that was produced during a great vintage year (1929) in the most celebrated part of the Cognac country, “Grand Fine Champagne”. It has remained in its unblended state in barrels from 1929 until the present date. Cognac of this calibre is hard to come by because no more than a few small growers have the patience and aptitude to put aside, year after year, a distillation of their outstanding vintage.

HINE FAMILY RESERVE 24.75 285.00

Since the early 19th Century, it has been the custom of the Hine Family to set aside the best Cognac produced during a particularly outstanding year for their own future use—ultimately, this old precious reserve is served to honored guests on special occasions. For the first time, Francios Hine, managing director of this venerable firm, has consented to part with a few of these treasured bottles— each is numbered and bears a back label relating the unique history of the contents, hand-signed by a Hine director. 14
